bug.short_desc: wrong radiobutton and checkbutton behavior in "view" menu
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: It is possible to have multiple radio buttons selected in the "view" menu.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): libreoffice-5.1.4.1-1.fc24.x86_64 gtk3-3.20.6-1.fc24.x86_64 abrt-2.8.1-1.fc24.x86_64 libreport-2.7.1-1.fc24.x86_64
How reproducible: always with Gtk3 backend
Steps to Reproduce: 1. open libreoffice 2. open a new impress (presentation) document 3. in "View" menu, select any other radio button but "Normal"
Actual results: For some radio buttons, two of them are selected at the same time. This affects e.g: Normal+Outline or Notes+Slide Sorter, Normal+Slide Sorter, … For some other combinations of radio buttons, it just takes very long to change the selection. When hiding the menu and then showing it again, you see the previous selection.
Expected results: In a group of radio buttons, exactly one button must be selected, not more. Menu should immediately react to changes.

This is also true for CheckButtons. 1. have a selected CheckButton 2. unselect it 3. open the menu again
What happens: CheckButton shows being selected but behaves correctly (as if it were unselected)
What should happen: CheckButton should present its state.
This issue is also present with other backends such as SAL_USE_VCLPLUGIN=kde4.
Blah. Apparently the handling of normal vs. master modes has been redone, but the special code in the menu for switching from a master mode back to normal has stayed as it was...
Actually the DisplayModeToolbarMenu was added for this change. So it's likely just buggy...

Other than that, when selecting "View" → "Slide Master", it often gets back to "View" → "Normal".
